<title>Use Specification Files</title>

If you think that you will frequently run a paradata concatenation on the same set of files, then you can use a specification file that contains the parameters of the concatenation. Once you have <link specify_logs.csdoc>specified</link> the input and output logs, then you can select <b>Save As</b> from the <b>File</b> menu. This will create a <link CSPro::program_information_file_pff.csdoc>PFF file</link> with the specified settings.

From the same <b>File</b> menu, you can select <b>Open</b> to load the parameters from a PFF file.

Having a PFF that describes your program parameters also allows you to run a <link run_production_paradata_concatenates.csdoc>production concatenation</link>.
